import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['Year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['Year'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['Year'])]
    data['Year'] = data['Year'].dt.year

    plt.plot(data['Year'], data['Deaths'])
    plt.xlabel('Year')
    plt.ylabel('Deaths')
    plt.title('What is the trend of deaths over the years?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend(['Deaths'])
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)

    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data_grouped = data.groupby('Entity')['Deaths'].sum().reset_index()
    data_grouped = data_grouped.sort_values('Deaths', ascending=False)

    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    plt.bar(data_grouped['Entity'], data_grouped['Deaths'])
    plt.xlabel('Entity')
    plt.ylabel('Deaths')
    plt.xticks(rotation=90)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of deaths across different entities?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['Year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['Year'], format='%Y', errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['Year'])]
    
    avg_deaths = data['Deaths'].mean()
    
    plt.plot(data['Year'], data['Deaths'], label='Deaths')
    plt.axhline(avg_deaths, color='red', linestyle='--', label=f'Average Deaths: {avg_deaths:.2f}')
    
    plt.xlabel('Year')
    plt.ylabel('Deaths')
    plt.title('What is the average number of deaths per year?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['Year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['Year'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['Year'])]
    data['Year'] = data['Year'].dt.year
    data = data.groupby('Year')['Deaths'].sum().reset_index()
    data['Percentage Change'] = data['Deaths'].pct_change() * 100

    plt.plot(data['Year'], data['Percentage Change'], label='Percentage Change', color='blue')
    plt.xlabel('Year')
    plt.ylabel('Percentage Change in Deaths')
    plt.title('What is the percentage change in deaths over the years?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    scatter = ax.scatter(data['Entity'], data['Deaths'], alpha=0.5)
    ax.set_xlabel('Entity')
    ax.set_ylabel('Deaths')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.title('What is the correlation between entity and deaths?', wrap=True)
    legend1 = ax.legend(*scatter.legend_elements(), title="Entities")
    ax.add_artist(legend1)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
